<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 03 at 4:18PM EDT  by NWS Blacksburg</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of
Pulaski, south central Giles, east central Bland, northeastern Wythe
and west central Montgomery Counties and the City of Radford through
445 PM EDT...
At 417 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Parrott, or near Poplar Hill, moving southwest at 35 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Radford...
Pulaski...
Dublin...
Max Meadows...
Poplar Hill...
Mechanicsburg...
and Eggleston.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
